04]]\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#fff3f3;\"|16.3% &nbsp; ''56,701''\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#edffff;\"|'''81.8%''' ''283,994''\n| style=\"background:#def;\"|[[John Kerry]] || style=\"background:#fff3f3;\"|[[George W. Bush]]\n| style=\"background:#ffd588;\"|[[New York City mayoral elections#2005|2005]]|| style=\"background:#def;\"|[[Fernando Ferrer]], D || style=\"background:#fff3f3;\"|[[Mike Bloomberg]], R/Lib-[[Independence Party of New York|Indep'ce]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#ff7;\"|[[U.S. presidential election, 2000|2000]]\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#fff3f3;\"|11.8% &nbsp; ''36,245''\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#edffff;\"|'''86.3%''' ''265,801''\n| style=\"background:#def;\"|[[Al Gore]] || style=\"background:#fff3f3;\"|[[George W. Bush]]\n| style=\"background:#ffd588;\"|[[New York City mayoral elections#2001|2001]]|| style=\"background:#def;\"|[[Mark J. Green|Mark Green]],<br />D-[[Working Families Party|Working Families]]|| style=\"background:#fff3f3;\"|[[Michael Bloomberg]],<br />R-[[Independence Party of New York|Independence]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#ff7;\"|[[U.S. presidential election, 1996|1996]]\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#fff3f3;\"|10.5% &nbsp; ''30,435''\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#edffff;\"|'''85.8%''' ''248,276''\n| style=\"background:#def;\"|[[Bill Clinton]] || style=\"background:#edffff;\"|[[Bill Clinton]]\n| style=\"background:#ffd588;\"| [[New York City mayoral elections#1997|1997]]|| style=\"background:#def;\"|[[Ruth Messinger]], D|| style=\"background:#fff3f3;\"|[[Rudolph Giuliani]], R-Liberal\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#ff7;\"|[[U.S. presidential election, 1992|1992]]\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#fff3f3;\"|20.7% &nbsp; ''63,310''\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#edffff;\"|'''73.7%''' ''225,038''\n| style=\"background:#def;\"|[[Bill Clinton]]|| style=\"background:#edffff;\"|[[Bill 