'''[[Equestrianism|equestrian]]''' competitions at the [[2017 Southeast Asian Games]] in [[Kuala Lumpur]] were held at International Endurance and Putrajaya Equestrian Park.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kualalumpur2017.com.my/seagames-sport.cshtml?cid=36|title=KL 2017: Equestrian|publisher=[[2017 Southeast Asian Games|KL 2017]]|accessdate=13 February 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170214181530/http://www.kualalumpur2017.com.my/seagames-sport.cshtml?cid=36|archive-date=14 February 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nThe 2017 Games feature competitions in six events (all events for mixed).\n\n==Events==\nThe following events will be contested:\n{|\n|\n*'''Dressage'''\n**Individual\n**Team\n*'''Endurance'''\n**Individual\n**Team\n*'''Show Jumping'''\n**Individual\n**Team\n|}\n\n===Schedule===\n\n==Participation==\n===Participating nations===\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* {{flagSEAGF|BRU|2017|}}\n* {{flagSEAGF|CAM|2017|}}\n* {{flagSEAGF|INA|2017|}}\n* {{flagSEAGF|LAO|2017|}}\n* {{flagSEAGF|MAS|2017|}}\n* {{flagSEAGF|MYA|2017|}}\n* {{flagSEAGF|PHI|2017|}}\n* {{flagSEAGF|SIN|2017|}}\n* {{flagSEAGF|THA|2017|}}\n* {{flagSEAGF|TLS|2017|}}\n* {{flagSEAGF|VIE|2017|}}\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Medal summary==\n===Medal table===\n{{Color box|#ccccff|border=darkgray}} Host nation (Malaysia)\n\n{{Medals table\n | caption        = \n | host           = \n | flag_template  = flagSEAGF\n | event          = 2017\n | team           = \n | gold_MAS = 6 | silver_MAS = 3 | bronze_MAS = 0 | host_MAS = yes \n | gold_THA = 0 | silver_THA = 3 | bronze_THA = 1\n | gold_SGP = 0 | silver_SGP = 0 | bronze_SGP = 2\n | gold_BRU = 0 | silver_BRU = 0 | bronze_BRU = 1\n | gold_CAM = 0 | silver_CAM = 0 | bronze_CAM = 1\n | gold_INA = 0 | silver_INA = 0 | bronze_INA = 1\n}}\n\n===Medalists===\n{| {{MedalistTable|type=Event|width=250}}\n|-\n|Individual dressage<br />{{DetailsLink|Equestrian at the 2017 Southeast Asian Games \u2013 Individual dressage}}\n|{{flagSEAGFmedalist|Quzandria Nur Mahamad